    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-17T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2216</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MCK1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moser</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-17T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 3, 3 p.m., somewhat garbled. As emergency measure and without
                    commitment to permanent support Red Cross authorizes you to draw up to $5,000.
                    Meanwhile please report: (1) Organization <pb facs="0184" n="134"
                        xml:id="pg_134"/> and competence of personnel Harbin Red Cross Chapter; (2)
                    any additional funds urgent now; (3) probable requirements both material and
                    financial for 30,000 refugees in Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
